text.section:
Any registered owner or lessee of a fleet of vehicles may apply to the cabinet for a permit to establish at his own expense a fleet inspection station. The cabinet shall not issue any fleet inspection station permit until it has found that the applicant:
Maintains an established place of business or facility for the repair and maintenance of the applicant's fleet of vehicles;
Has obtained machinery, tools, and equipment approved by the cabinet and adequate to conduct the required emissions inspections;
Employs properly trained personnel with whom to perform the necessary labor; and
Will keep complete records of all inspections performed and repairs made and will provide the information or data to the cabinet.
